tidbits.text: Japantown was much larger before interment in 1942. This model, in the window of the Nikkei Legacy Center, gives a sense of its size, and the kind of businesses that served this community.
tidbits.title: Model of Japantown

tidbits.title: New Market Building

tidbits.text: Chapman and Lownsdale Squares were the site of labor protests long before the parks were occupied in 2011.
tidbits.title: Before Occupy

tidbits.text: Highway 99W, also known as Harbor Drive, was demolished in 1974 to make way for a riverside park. The park is named Tom McCall Waterfront Park, in honor of Oregon governor Tom McCall.
tidbits.title: The Freeway that Became a Park
